Srivastava","email":"904a07f5d5a3adde1e4d458a4465bbe1e0df36dc@polymagelabs.com"},"message":"[MLIR][TF][SCF] Introduce tf.IfRegion -> scf.if lowering

Lowering for `tf.IfRegion` -> `scf.if` implemented in a new pass
`convert-tf-control-flow-to-scf`, which is added in
`tensorflow/transforms` and can be used for all direct control flow
lowerings from the TensorFlow dialect to the SCF dialect (without going
through dialects like HLO, which involve tuples, for example). Currently
this pass has one pattern `ConvertIfRegionOp`. It lowers the
`tf.IfRegion` op to `scf.if`.

Signed-off-by: Srishti Srivastava <srishti.srivastava@polymagelabs.com>","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/GulajavaMinistudio/tensorflow/commits/d305672f9d6d42d04786152393e066780b32ce8d"},{"sha":"588b1261b8798522008f3daebccc02087835fb09","author":{"name":"Jacques Pienaar","email":"8b5f536c3e2f2b8ae266b27bc9085a584b5bd904@google.com"},"message":"Update accessors to be more consistent.

getOperands make the intent clearer while getOperand(idx) is more idiomatic than operands()[idx].
